\details{
Key features of \code{zztable1} include:
\itemize{
\item \strong{Stratification:} Generate summaries by treatment groups or stratified
by a third variable (e.g., study sites).
\item \strong{P-Value Calculation:} Perform statistical tests (e.g., Fisher's exact test
for categorical variables, linear regression for numeric variables) to include
p-values for group comparisons.
\item \strong{Handling Missing Data:} Explicitly represent missing data in summaries and
calculations where applicable.
\item \strong{Descriptive Statistics:} Compute means, standard deviations, and percentages
for numeric and categorical variables.
\item \strong{Customizable Outputs:} Output tables in LaTeX or HTML with themes and
styles suitable for publication.
\item \strong{Integration with Tidyverse:} Seamless compatibility with \code{dplyr} and other
tidyverse tools for streamlined data manipulation.
}

The package uses a modular design with generic methods for flexibility.
